  • Constructor Details

    • Layer

      public Layer(long buildingID, long floorID, long layerID, JLabel parent, User currUser) throws IOException, org.json.simple.parser.ParseException
      Constructs a Layer object with the given buildingID, floorID, layerID, parent JLabel, and current user. Reads the appropriate POIs from the POI.json file and adds them to the POIList.
      Parameters:
      buildingID - the ID of the building that this layer belongs to
      floorID - the ID of the floor that this layer belongs to
      layerID - the ID of this layer
      parent - the parent JLabel of this layer
      currUser - the current user who is logged in
      Throws:
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs while reading the POI.json file
      org.json.simple.parser.ParseException - if the POI.json file contains invalid JSON syntax

    • readJSON

      public void readJSON(long bID, long fID) throws IOException, org.json.simple.parser.ParseException
      Reads the JSON file and adds POIs to POIList if they have the same id as this layer.
      Parameters:
      bID - The id of the building the POI belongs to.
      fID - The id of the floor the POI belongs to.
      Throws:
      IOException - If there is an error reading the JSON file.
      org.json.simple.parser.ParseException - If there is an error parsing the JSON file.
